clues.clue: This is a great place start to the fair, and full of friendly faces.
clues.hint: You can find loads of useful INFO here.

clues.clue: Where the youngest 4-Hers prep for 4-H.
clues.hint: The clubs in this tent are aimed at grades K-3.

clues.clue: Want to learn how this app was made? Come and stop by, we'd love to chat.
clues.hint: Check the app settings to see who made it. If you ever get stuck, we're here to help too!

clues.clue: This tent is where plastic and metal come to compete.
clues.hint: And where LEGOs and machines clash. Wall-E anybody?

clues.clue: Moo-ve on over to meet the gentle giants of the fair!
clues.hint: To make a cheeseburger, you'll need the help of these.

clues.clue: Look for a tent racing past many checked flags.
clues.hint: These racers aren't in the cars, but controlling them from afar.

clues.clue: This animal tent comes first in the alphabet.
clues.hint: Not a llama but an ___.

clues.clue: These furry and feathered friends are small but mighty cute!
clues.hint: They are common household pets but you still might find them in your backyard.

clues.clue: This tent is where you can find your feathered friends.
clues.hint: Cluck, cluck, cluck! There's also some animals that like to go swimming here.

clues.clue: Take a break, enjoy a show, and refuel for more adventure.
clues.hint: This 4-H run food tent plays music while you enjoy your treats.

clues.clue: These clubs will sharpen your aim and test your skills!
clues.hint: Bullseye!

clues.clue: Slither on over to meet these fascinating creatures!
clues.hint: This tent is full of scales, fins, and tails.

clues.clue: Where could you go to figure out what's "bugging" your plants?
clues.hint: Learn the secrets of a green thumb from the experts!

clues.clue: Is it a "kid"? A baby ___? What? It's both!
clues.hint: Some have horns, but they all eat poison ivy.

clues.clue: Can you hear the tail-wagging excitement?
clues.hint: "Man's best friend" awaits.

clues.clue: Sometimes they don't like the shoes we buy them... they just kick them off!
clues.hint: Where would you look for the state animal?

clues.clue: Buzz on over to where nature's sweet nectar flows!
clues.hint: Pollinators are hard at work here.

clues.clue: I'm gonna chug, I'm gonna choo, I'll be stopping at a station near you.
clues.hint: The only problem is they aren't full scale...

clues.clue: Baa-lieve it or not, these animals are also ruminants.
clues.hint: They're experts at cloud impressions, but their wool is real.

clues.clue: If we're in a fairytale, this might be over a moat.
clues.hint: Look for the structure connecting two sides.

clues.clue: Some clubs get tied up in 4-H, this club gets Tangled!
clues.hint: When they're not performing on the stage, you can find them here.
